EXT. DAY: OHIO STATE REFORMATORY COURTYARD 3
Daniels' car rolls to a stop outside the reformatory; he's 
let out to see rows of policemen holding back a mob of fiery 
onlookers, clearing a path up the road to the doors.
Several policemen move a handcuffed Daniels up the stairs, 
who smiles arrogantly at the people surrounding him.
ROBERT DANIELS:
(to crowd)
Give me credit. Give me credit for all 
the Niebels!
CROWD:
Kill him! Lynch him!
ROBERT DANIELS:
Fuck you all! Go back home!
CROWD:
Give him the fuckin chair!
CROWD:
Kill the rat right now!
Daniels enters the front lobby cackling with laughter. As the 
doors close behind him the mob overwhelms the police outside.
INT. DAY: FRONT LOBBY OF OHIO STATE REFORMATORY 4
Commotion echoes even louder when Daniels enters the 
building; dozens of policemen, reporters and attorneys are 
packed into the tiled lobby.
REPORTER:
Picture! Picture for the press!
ROBERT DANIELS:
(to crowd)
Wait till I get my collar straight. 
How 'bout I pose with a gun in my 
hand.
Daniels leans back and cartoonishly points a handgun at the 
sky. The camera snaps and a bright flash goes off.
Two policemen forcefully move Daniels to a hallway at the end 
of the room. Shaffer faces the newsmen.

